---

<BaseLayout
  title="Martial Arts CRM (2026)"
  description="Martial arts CRM for lead management and student retention. Track prospects, automate follow-ups, identify risks, and build lasting relationships with students."
>
  <!-- Breadcrumbs -->
  <BreadcrumbsEnhanced
    site="mydojo"
    items={[
      { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
      { label: 'Martial Arts CRM', href: '/martial-arts-crm/' }
    ]}
  />

  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="section bg-white">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
        <span class="inline-block px-4 py-2 mb-4 text-sm font-semibold text-brand-red bg-brand-red-light rounded-full">Complete Guide</span>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-4">Martial Arts CRM</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600">
          Lead management and student retention tools for martial arts schools. Automate follow-ups, track engagement, identify risks, and build lasting student relationships.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Featured Answer -->
  <FeaturedAnswer question="What is a martial arts CRM?">
    A martial arts CRM (Customer Relationship Management) system tracks prospects and students through their entire journey—from initial inquiry through trial class, enrollment, and ongoing training. It automates lead follow-ups, manages trial class workflows, identifies retention risks, and provides timeline visibility into every student relationship. Martial arts CRMs understand belt progression, family relationships, and multi-year student lifecycles unlike generic sales CRMs.
  </FeaturedAnswer>

  <!-- Statistics Section -->
  <StatisticsSection
    site="mydojo"
    pageUrl="https://mydojo.software/martial-arts-crm/"
    title="Martial Arts CRM Impact Statistics"
    stats={crmStats}
  />

  <!-- Main Content -->
  <section class="section bg-white">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto prose prose-lg">

        <h2>Lead Management and Student Relationship Tools</h2>

        <p>
          Every martial arts school faces the same fundamental challenge: converting interested prospects into enrolled students, then nurturing those students into long-term members. A martial arts CRM system provides the infrastructure to manage both sides of this equation systematically.
        </p>

        <p>
          Unlike generic CRM platforms designed for sales teams or retail businesses, martial arts CRM functionality addresses the specific journey from initial inquiry through trial class, enrollment, and ongoing retention. These tools recognize that a martial arts student relationship spans years rather than single transactions.
        </p>

        <h3>CRM Functions in Martial Arts</h3>

        <p><strong>Lead Management:</strong></p>
        <p>
          Handles the pre-enrollment phase—capturing inquiries, nurturing prospects, scheduling trials, and converting interested parties into paying students. This front-end function directly impacts school growth.
        </p>

        <p><strong>Student Relationship Management:</strong></p>
        <p>
          Addresses the post-enrollment phase—tracking engagement, identifying retention risks, managing communications, and building the long-term relationships that create lifetime students.
        </p>

        <p>
          Effective martial arts CRM integrates both functions, creating continuity from first contact through years of training.
        </p>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Comparison Table -->
  <section class="section bg-gray-50">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
        <ComparisonTable
          title="Martial Arts CRM vs Generic CRM vs Manual Tracking"
          headers={['MyDojo (Martial Arts CRM)', 'Generic CRM', 'Spreadsheets/Email']}
          rows={comparisonData}
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Features Section -->
  <section class="section bg-white">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto prose prose-lg">

        <h2>Essential CRM Features for Martial Arts Schools</h2>

        <h3>1. Lead Management</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Automated lead capture from website, Facebook, and phone</li>
          <li>Instant lead response with confirmation and information</li>
          <li>Lead source tracking for marketing ROI</li>
          <li>Automated follow-up sequences</li>
          <li>Trial class scheduling workflow</li>
          <li>Lead pipeline visualization by stage</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>2. Trial Class Management</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Trial booking with automated confirmations</li>
          <li>Pre-trial communication sequences</li>
          <li>Trial day check-in and feedback capture</li>
          <li>Post-trial enrollment follow-up automation</li>
          <li>Trial show rate tracking</li>
          <li>Trial-to-member conversion analytics</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>3. Student Engagement Tracking</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Attendance pattern monitoring</li>
          <li>Engagement score calculation</li>
          <li>Retention risk identification</li>
          <li>Automated at-risk alerts for instructors</li>
          <li>Progress milestone tracking</li>
          <li>Student lifecycle timeline view</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>4. Communication Management</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Multi-channel communication (SMS, email, in-app)</li>
          <li>Segmented messaging by rank, program, or status</li>
          <li>Automated campaigns for re-engagement</li>
          <li>Communication history per student</li>
          <li>Template library for common messages</li>
          <li>Scheduled send for optimal timing</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>5. Analytics and Reporting</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Lead conversion funnel analysis</li>
          <li>Lead source ROI tracking</li>
          <li>Retention rate by cohort</li>
          <li>Student lifetime value calculation</li>
          <li>Engagement trends over time</li>
          <li>Marketing attribution reporting</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Related Resources</h2>

        <ul>
          <li><a href="/martial-arts-software/">Martial Arts Software Overview</a> — Complete platform features</li>
          <li><a href="/blog/martial-arts-marketing-tips/">Marketing Tips</a> — Lead generation strategies</li>
          <li><a href="/blog/member-retention-strategies/">Retention Strategies</a> — Keep students training longer</li>
          <li><a href="/blog/lead-generation-mma-gyms/">Lead Generation Guide</a> — MMA gym marketing</li>
          <li><a href="/martial-arts-billing-software/">Billing Software</a> — Payment processing integration</li>
        </ul>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <FAQEnhanced
    site="mydojo"
    pageUrl="https://mydojo.software/martial-arts-crm/"
    title="Frequently Asked Questions About Martial Arts CRM"
    faqs={faqItems}
  />

  <!-- CTA Section -->
  <section class="section bg-brand-red text-white">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Ready to Improve Your Lead Conversion?</h2>
        <p class="text-xl mb-8 opacity-95">
          See how MyDojo CRM can transform your lead management with automated follow-ups, retention tracking, and engagement analytics.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
          <a href="/contact/" class="btn-primary-large bg-white text-brand-red hover:bg-gray-100">Start Free Trial</a>
          <a href="/pricing/" class="btn-secondary-large border-white text-white hover:bg-white hover:bg-opacity-10">View Pricing</a>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-6 text-sm opacity-90">No credit card required • 14-day free trial • Cancel anytime</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .section {
    padding: 4rem 0;
  }

  .prose {
    max-width: none;
  }

  .prose h2 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--brand-navy);
    margin-top: 3rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .prose h3 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--brand-navy);
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .prose p {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    color: #475569;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .prose ul {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  .prose li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    color: #475569;
  }

  .prose strong {
    color: var(--brand-navy);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .prose a {
    color: var(--brand-red);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .prose a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .btn-primary-large,
  .btn-secondary-large {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    padding: 1rem 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: all 0.2s;
  }

  .btn-primary-large:hover,
  .btn-secondary-large:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .btn-secondary-large {
    border: 2px solid;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .section {
      padding: 3rem 0;
    }

    .prose h2 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }

    .prose h3 {
      font-size: 1.25rem;
    }
  }
</style>
